## Documentation Conventions

- **Ubiquitous Language:** when this project develops its own load-bearing design vocabulary (three or four terms encoding design rules, or terms that start being defined inconsistently across files), maintain a single canonical glossary at `notes/ubiquitous-language.md` (or `docs/ubiquitous-language.md` if there is no `notes/`). Brief in-place mentions elsewhere link to it; the glossary owns the definition. See [`docs/ubiquitous-language.md`](docs/ubiquitous-language.md) for the full convention.
{% if not full_stack %}

